<DocsLayout title="Install" slug="usage/install" description="Install Skill Wiki — bun, Node 22+, the prime CLI, and the MCP server.">
  <h1>Install</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--fg-muted);">
    Skill Wiki ships as a set of npm packages. The CLI handles compile / publish /
    install; the MCP server exposes the compiled corpus to your agent.
  </p>

  <h2>Requirements</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Node 22+</strong> (<a href="https://nodejs.org" rel="noopener">nodejs.org</a>)</li>
    <li><strong>Bun 1.3+</strong> recommended (<a href="https://bun.sh" rel="noopener">bun.sh</a>) — much faster than Node for the compile step</li>
    <li>An MCP-capable client (Claude Code, Cursor, Continue, Aider, …)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Install the CLI</h2>
<pre><code>{`# Bun (recommended)
bun add -g @prime-lang/cli

# Or npm
npm install -g @prime-lang/cli

# Verify
prime --version
# → prime 0.1.0`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Install a Skill from the marketplace</h2>
<pre><code>{`# The flagship Skill — frontend-design
prime install @frontend-design

# A minimal example
prime install @recipes`}</code></pre>

  <p>
    By default Skills go into <code>./.primes/</code>. Use <code>--dir</code> to
    customise.
  </p>

  <h2>Boot the MCP server</h2>
<pre><code>{`# Stdio transport (for Claude Code / Cursor)
PRIME_DIR=./.primes/@recipes bunx @prime-lang/mcp-server-core

# HTTP transport (for browser-based clients)
PRIME_DIR=./.primes/@recipes \\
  bunx @prime-lang/mcp-server-core --http --port 4001`}</code></pre>

  <h2>From source</h2>
  <p>If you want to develop against Skill Wiki itself or run an unreleased version:</p>

<pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/skill-wiki/prime-system.git
cd prime-system
bun install
bun run build
bun run packages/cli/src/index.ts --version`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Verify the install</h2>
<pre><code>{`# Compile and inspect the bundled hello-world example
cd examples/hello-world
prime compile

# List atoms
prime list
# → @hello-world/method-make-tea         method
# → @hello-world/term-celsius            term
# → @hello-world/fact-water-boils-at-100c fact
# → @hello-world/rule-altitude-affects-boiling rule`}</code></pre>

